## Architecture reminders

- Finwiz = this local project; Finviz = data source (finviz.com / Elite)
- Core data: `data/tickers/*.json`, `data/index/search_index.json`, `config/toggles.json`
- Dashboard: Streamlit multi-page app in `dashboard/app.py`
- Elite sync: `scripts/sync_finviz_elite.py` / `scripts/finviz_elite.py`
- Price providers (`scripts/lib_market_data.py`): **LeanData → Massive → Alpaca → Tiingo → yfinance**
- LeanData reader: `scripts/lib_leandata.py` — DuckDB `F:\LeanData\data\depot.duckdb` + parquet under `MarketData/bars/{Day,1Hour,15Min,5Min,1Min}`
- PIT eligibility: `scripts/lib_pit_eligibility.py` — Massive/Benzinga ratings + income (+ Lean statements fallback); advanced default `--fundamentals-mode pit`
- Advanced backtest: `scripts/backtest_advanced.py` (IS/OOS + Monte Carlo); results → `data/backtests/advanced-latest.json`

## Trading path (agreed 2026-07-22)

- **Local paper fills** (`bot/broker_paper.py` → `bot/ledger/paper_ledger.json`) are **simulated only** — they do **not** appear on Alpaca Paper
- Alpaca keys today = **market data**, not order routing (`bot/config.json` broker=`none`; no `broker_alpaca_paper.py` yet)
- **Cursor MCP / Railway / LLM chat are research-only** — never the order path; execution stays rule-based (`action.rules.json` → signals → broker)
- Always-on = Windows task `FinwizScreenerAutomation` / `scripts/run_automation.ps1`, not “keep dashboard open” and not MCP
- **Agreed sequence:** local paper → **Alpaca Paper adapter (Phase 3)** with kill-switches → side-by-side compare → live only with explicit unlock + tiny size
- Treat stack as disciplined **when/whether** screener+execution, not a beat-B&H alpha engine

## Backtest verdict (committed 2026-07-22)

10y Lean Day + PIT on all 8 tickers (2016-07-22 → 2026-07-21):

- **Verdict:** risk-first filter, **not** an alpha engine vs buy-and-hold
- Strategy: +31% total / **~2.7% CAGR**, max DD **~−10%**, Sharpe **~0.5**, 351 trades, ~51% win rate
- OOS CAGR **~6.5%** > IS **~1.2%** (did not only curve-fit early years)
- Equal-weight buy-and-hold on same basket ~**41% CAGR** — SMA200 + Tight BUY + PIT keep capital out of mega-runs
- Use for **when/whether** to engage quality growth; do not expect timing to match B&H return on this set

```powershell
py -3 scripts\backtest_advanced.py --years 10 --provider lean --fundamentals-mode pit --resolution Day --tickers NVDA,CRDO,PLTR,LLY,AVGO,ANET,TSM,MU
```
